RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 39. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAYNT THE MOON vied for the lead, raced on the rail, was quickly joined by rivals to the out side, set the pace, worked in a set through the turn, was headed headed at the top of the lane, battled down the stretch repelled the challenger and picked up the win. CHATAIN'S EAGLE vied for the lead, ended up stalking the leader for a quarter of a mile, joined the early leader with another foe, racing inn the four path on the far outside, shook two of the other forwardly placed rivals, drew next to the early leader and challenged, battled down the lane, and tired late. WILD BIZNESS made no impact. MALLORI'S MAGIC was off the pace early on, settled in hands along the rail, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, was encouraged and asked slightly improved through the turn, was cued again at the quarter pole but had no late kick. BONJOOR MADEMOISEL was rank early, stumbled leaving the shoot, raced up in between foes briefly then tired. MY RAINBOW trailed through out.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 93. Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 5, 2022. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MILITARY BEARING was sharp out of the gates, had enough speed to pass rivals, take the lead and the rail going into the first turn, set the pace as he rated for the first half of a mile, was joined on the outside by stalking rivals, continued to show the way with two foes battling just off his hip, was given the ok at the five sixteenth pole and left his rivals behind and drew off to win as he pleased. THUNDERSHOOK stalked the early leaders from the four path, advanced at the half mile pole on the outside, joined the leaders after the half, battled with an inside foe through the turn and down the stretch, shook his rival and got up for second. GORDON ANTHONY stalked from the three path, drew in between rivals at the half mile pole, continued through the turn, lost touch with the eventual leader at the five sixteenth pole, battled with and outside foe into and down the lane and came up short. MOUNT KENYA was well off the pace early, made on run, launched a bid at the half, shifted out five wide, was in contention but had too much to do. DREWPOWER raced from off the pace, launched a bid at the half mile pole, angled out six wide, drew next to the early leaders on the far outside but made no impact. RACE.FOOTNOTES: C D'S WILD FIRE was off mid pack, raced behind horse, had a horse to his inside, was asked and responded giving good effort early on, was ridden up right behind the early leaders, took the dirt in has face as he kept responding to urging, was encouraged with a left handed crop and responded well from that and continued to gain ground, raced four wide in the stretch, continued to respond from left handing urging and finally had enough momentum to clear the last of the early leaders in deep stretch, race by and get up for the win. A very nicely ran race for a two year old. CUNIMBUS was off mid pack and raced off the pace early on, launched a bid at the half mile pole, responded and began to gain ground, was just behind the early leaders in the stretch, was angled out five wide late to get out of the dirt, and came up short. COOL RIDE was off in the middle of the pack, launched a bid at the half mile pole, in the four path, circled up on the outside, gained ground, was in the lead at the quarter pole, continued to lead down the stretch, and tired late. LOUDTHUNDRHEVYRAIN was well off the pace early, raced five wide, bid at the half, was gaining ground, was still well off the early leaders entering the stretch, stayed five wide and had clean racing room, continued to close extremely fast, but it was not enough today.
